Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.73,0:00:07.11,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\a6\blur3}On the first Sunday of the autumn school term,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.19,0:00:13.28,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\a6\blur3}Dr. Agasa was taking us back home after watching a movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.95,0:00:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's exactly 2 PM!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.37,0:00:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just saw the clock change to saying 2 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.29,0:00:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.83,0:00:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}, you're too loud!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.55,0:00:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look...! On top of that building!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.71,0:00:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.76,0:00:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.26,0:00:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fighting up there's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:43.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was pushed off!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.12,0:01:08.92,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers,\Nhe solves every mystery and code!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:13.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A mysterious slow-motion descent, and the surprising mystery of the time lag!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.05,0:01:14.63,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.63,0:01:16.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.59,0:01:18.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.08,0:03:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, is the person who made the report here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.59,0:03:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.76,0:03:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was shopping, and I passed by here when...{lightning flashed and he fell.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.15,0:03:41.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I quickly called 119.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.36,0:03:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.86,0:03:44.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.41,0:03:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.74,0:03:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a suicide attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.87,0:03:50.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nor was it an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone pushed him off the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.12,0:03:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Sakai, from the Beika Emergency Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The accidental fall that was reported earlier may have been a murder attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.26,0:04:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was 37 year-old Masa'aki Ogata-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.43,0:04:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His address is Central Beika...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.39,0:04:17.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, miss, it was around 2:10 when you called the ambulance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.77,0:04:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hunh? Yeah, it was 2:10 exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.24,0:04:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't have been more than five or six minutes ago that the ambulance arrived, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's around 2:20 now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.33,0:04:40.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{The average time for an ambulance to arrive after being requested is five to six minutes, so by subtracting that time, you can estimate the time of the report.}An ambulance usually takes 5 to 6 minutes to arrive, so by subtracting that time, you can estimate when it was requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.92,0:04:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We saw him being pushed off at...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly 2 PM!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:54.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. In other words, he took ten minutes to fall — way too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:04:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since this building can't be more than five storeys...{it couldn't take ten minutes.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.07,0:05:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mitsuhiko, was this building this short before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it had at least five storeys...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.45,0:05:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.49,0:05:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.24,0:05:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wa... Hey, wait! There's a lift here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.91,0:05:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:18.83,Signs,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of order...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This spot is right above where he landed, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.18,0:05:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.97,0:05:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lowest two floors stick out slightly, making a balcony on the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it now. After being pushed down from here, the man first fell on the balcony, and then to the ground from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.53,0:05:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why it took ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.20,0:05:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was pushed off twice, poor guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.37,0:05:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's search inside the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:59.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lady we talked to earlier said nobody left the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already been at least ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.50,0:06:04.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit could've escaped through the back door...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:08.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The back door! Maybe there's some clues to the culprit there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.01,0:06:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.09,0:06:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, you guys...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.31,0:06:17.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe we should take a look at that balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.10,0:06:20.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Based on the position, it should be this flat...
Comment: 0,0:06:21.35,0:06:23.36,Signs,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.77,0:06:23.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Ogata Finances'?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.86,0:06:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the victim also...{named Ogata?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.44,0:06:29.20,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The victim was 37 year-old Masa'aki Ogata-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps this is his office.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:34.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.20,0:06:34.33,Signs,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.33,0:06:34.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.45,0:06:34.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was a moneylender...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.33,0:06:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-hey, Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.83,0:06:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This looks like it was the initial crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We finally found the back door...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's chain-locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.13,0:06:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the culprit couldn't have escaped through the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how did they escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must've had quite a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.10,0:07:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really don't think we should be in there without permission...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A driver's license?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Ryōhei Honda'... Since it's on this upended sofa, maybe he was involved in the fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.04,0:07:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And maybe he was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.04,0:07:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too early to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:25.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, you two...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.67,0:07:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fire escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.92,0:07:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit must've escaped through the emergency exit on the third floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.76,0:07:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all muddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.14,0:07:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no footprints, not even one...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.23,0:07:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.73,0:07:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they didn't use the front door, the back door, or the fire escape, then how did they get away?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.15,0:07:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I doubt there's any other way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.49,0:07:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit must still be inside the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.83,0:07:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiding somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:00.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's tell Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.04,0:08:00.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.91,0:08:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:06.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want us to find the culprit without him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.92,0:08:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.55,0:08:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Marks of something being dragged.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.88,0:08:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's a bloodstain too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.59,0:08:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit must've dragged the victim in here temporarily after he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.47,0:08:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then dropped him from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.65,0:08:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They look like the ones that Honda wore in his licence photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.11,0:08:36.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They couldn't be outside the balcony unless the victim, Ogata-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.82,0:08:40.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,happened to take them from Honda the moment he was pushed off, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.29,0:08:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If those glasses do belong to this 'Honda', then we have ourselves a culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.63,0:08:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess there's no work for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.50,0:08:55.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he planned to throw him off again, why would the culprit bother carrying Ogata-{\i1}san{\i0} in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.68,0:08:58.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For what reason...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.89,0:09:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the ones who saw Masa'aki Ogata-{\i1}san{\i0} being pushed off?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.19,0:09:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, you shouldn't mess with a crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should know better, Agasa-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.69,0:09:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How embarrassing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.99,0:09:18.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since you've come all the way here, this Ogata-{\i1}san{\i0} must be somebody special.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:22.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a notorious loan shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a pair of glasses on the outside of the balcony.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.29,0:09:30.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A driver's license?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.96,0:09:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ryōhei Honda...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.46,0:09:36.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ryōhei... Honda...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like these glasses belong to him as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's quite likely he's the one who visited and fought with Ogata-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.98,0:09:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's check with the officer dealing with his file.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.44,0:09:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.69,0:09:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go check the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.49,0:10:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should tell the police that the culprit's still here instead of searching ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.12,0:10:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's keep going, we can't give up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.71,0:10:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.92,0:10:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.09,0:10:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel like if we just keep looking, we might be able to expose the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.47,0:10:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.22,0:10:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go look on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.10,0:10:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll search the basement!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.56,0:10:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's start the investigation!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.15,0:10:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You haven't been able to locate Ryōhei Honda-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.82,0:10:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it. Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.16,0:10:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently he left home around noon without saying where he was going, and hasn't returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.08,0:10:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, he met up with an old acquaintance, so they think he may have headed to see him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.21,0:10:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks pretty certain, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.92,0:10:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, something doesn't fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.34,0:11:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he drag him in here then take him back out?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rubber boots?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.14,0:11:11.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing odd about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.10,0:11:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not with this much rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.44,0:11:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this receipt's from last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.02,0:11:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday's forecast said today would be clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.95,0:11:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody in this room either...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobody's hiding up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.20,0:11:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was fast — did you make sure to check properly?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.75,0:11:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.92,0:11:36.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.59,0:11:37.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that scream?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.75,0:11:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.26,0:11:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she'd go check the basement!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.97,0:11:43.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ayumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.51,0:11:47.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi-{\i1}kun{\i0}, are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.35,0:11:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshida-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.35,0:11:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Ayumi-{\i1}chan{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.69,0:11:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I saw a mouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.56,0:11:58.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you didn't get bitten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.78,0:12:03.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never mind that, I'm glad you weren't caught by the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.36,0:12:04.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.66,0:12:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, Honda wouldn't still be here—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.24,0:12:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honda?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.08,0:12:10.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You already identified who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.45,0:12:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er, not quite...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.75,0:12:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the only car here, so it must be Ogata's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.88,0:12:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.46,0:12:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rubber boots?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.51,0:12:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.51,0:12:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Together with a very interesting item.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A shovel...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think of a way to use those two objects...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.72,0:12:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a rather short list, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.77,0:12:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No clues on the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:42.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is someone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.65,0:12:46.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're there, please answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.62,0:12:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who is this Honda-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.38,0:13:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know too, right, doc?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.50,0:13:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too early to say for sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.68,0:13:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.30,0:13:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's you, Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.93,0:13:12.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Caught? Who was caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.64,0:13:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got caught... by the culprit...{（千葉）俺がです　犯人に。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.48,0:13:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! By the culprit?!{何！　犯人！？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.53,0:13:26.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, don't come any closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.28,0:13:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said I wanted a getaway car!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.83,0:13:32.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it really was you, Honda.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.33,0:13:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he's that Honda guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the perpetrator really {\i1}was{\i0} still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.83,0:13:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.30,0:13:39.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.84,0:13:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would this man behave like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.84,0:13:47.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, Honda? Why did you try to kill Ogata?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.93,0:13:51.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.77,0:13:54.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know... anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.27,0:13:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's lost his memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.56,0:13:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amnesia?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:02.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's why he...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.73,0:14:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not the kind of man to do something like this, Honda.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.66,0:14:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was the one who arrested you eight years ago as a robbery suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.25,0:14:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me? Robbery?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.58,0:14:20.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You committed a robbery along with a man you said you happened to meet at a bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.79,0:14:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with the only clue to his identity being that he had a hoarse voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.51,0:14:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we could never find your accomplice, and you alone ended up serving a sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.97,0:14:34.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you completely reformed after serving your term!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.10,0:14:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's not all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.68,0:14:44.78,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,After taking over your father's {small-scale }factory, you supported ex-convicts like you were by offering them jobs as factory workers!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a really nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.91,0:14:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.66,0:14:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.32,0:14:55.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So how did you end up committing crimes again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.66,0:14:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What connection did you have with Ogata?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.83,0:15:01.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's right. What connection did he have with the victim...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.63,0:15:05.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:11.85,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yesterday, he met up with an old acquaintance, so they think he may have headed to see him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.76,0:15:13.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:27.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see! So that's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.65,0:15:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honda! What happened between you and Ogata?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, I don't remember anything at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.00,0:15:43.54,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:49.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realised I must've been fighting with someone else there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:54.22,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did I...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.81,0:15:58.06,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did I push him down from up here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.60,0:16:01.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was scared of being caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.65,0:16:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my head hurt and I felt dizzy, so I decided to hide for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.07,0:16:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then just when I managed to get moving again...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.58,0:16:18.87,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No clues on the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.45,0:16:22.46,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is someone there? I'm with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.92,0:16:23.83,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The police?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.34,0:16:27.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to get caught...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.46,0:16:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did I try to kill that man to begin with?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.59,0:16:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he himself doesn't even know why he did it, there's no way we could, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:39.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which means we'll need a detective to solve this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did I try to kill him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.36,0:16:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.07,0:16:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You visited Masa'aki Ogata because he was an old acquaintance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.78,0:16:55.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An old... acquaintance?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:17:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi, did Masa'aki Ogata have a hoarse voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.66,0:17:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah, hoarse and intimidating.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.87,0:17:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think back, Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.63,0:17:12.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the man with the hoarse voice you met eight years ago at a bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.88,0:17:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.47,0:17:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man with the hoarse voice from eight years ago...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.06,0:17:24.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man with the hoarse voice I met at a bar...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.35,0:17:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.81,0:17:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd completely changed his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.15,0:17:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\t(2060,2273,\3c&HFFFFFF\4c&HFFFFFF)}But... that voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:35.41,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll follow you to hell to make you pay if I have to!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.91,0:17:38.45,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Do you get it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.95,0:17:40.87,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.46,0:17:45.96,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It really is you, isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.17,0:17:51.67,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It may have been eight years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:54.17,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the statute of limitations still hasn't expired.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.17,0:17:55.68,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So you want me to turn myself in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.13,0:18:01.68,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you atone for your crime, you can live a dignified life without the weight of it hanging upon you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.27,0:18:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to make him give himself up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.40,0:18:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I thought, he's a good guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.40,0:18:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.28,0:18:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That nice guy has...{Takagi hostage...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.69,0:18:17.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So how did you end up trying to murder Ogata?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:19.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.53,0:18:21.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the other way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.87,0:18:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew about Masa'aki Ogata's evil deeds, so he wanted you gone from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.92,0:18:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He planned to murder you, take your corpse deep into the mountains and bury you there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:36.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He prepared by inviting you here to this building,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.84,0:18:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which was empty as it was the weekend, and carried out his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.47,0:18:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he failed to kill you, and ended up having to push you off the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.32,0:18:56.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then when we saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.28,0:18:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone being pushed off...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.11,0:18:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Honda-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.32,0:19:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Masa'aki Ogata dragged you into his office to finish you off, Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.71,0:19:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As proof of that, look. Your jacket's all dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.08,0:19:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wasn't it Ogata who landed on the ground?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.92,0:19:17.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.09,0:19:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0} was unconscious from a strong blow to the head, hard enough to give him amnesia,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.56,0:19:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so he couldn't have pushed Masa'aki Ogata off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.14,0:19:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means there was only one possible course of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.06,0:19:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masa'aki Ogata intended to hide his corpse in the mountains after finishing him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.07,0:19:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For that plan to succeed, he had to remove every trace of Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}'s visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:48.75,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, I should get rid of that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.37,0:19:51.04,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Where's his glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.75,0:19:52.83,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.67,0:19:57.34,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, there they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.34,0:20:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as it being easy to slip because of the rain, remember what happened right at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:19.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, rather than one person falling off twice, the person who was falling changed midway!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.78,0:20:21.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over a ten-minute timespan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.78,0:20:26.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's the truth behind the long-winded fall, huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.17,0:20:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.09,0:20:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honda, you may not have done anything to Masa'aki Ogata...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.43,0:20:48.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you did attack and take Detective Chiba hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:49.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.77,0:20:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.81,0:20:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.15,0:20:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.02,0:20:56.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.77,0:20:59.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel sorry for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.15,0:20:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.11,0:21:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.28,0:21:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is something even I can't do anything about.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.20,0:21:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if he had was panicking and had lost his memory, that doesn't excuse his actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.83,0:21:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, he probably understands that better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.92,0:21:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for troubling you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.84,0:21:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.59,0:21:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about the handcuffs. I know you won't resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.84,0:21:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But before that, we've got to take you to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.51,0:21:32.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to have your head injuries treated, Honda-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.10,0:21:43.57,Narr,,10,10,0,,{\blur3}It wasn't long before Masa'aki Ogata was arrested as a suspect to the robbery eight years ago, and his recent attempt to murder Honda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.15,0:23:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Dr. Agasa did a great job once again, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.53,0:23:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.20,0:23:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could say that...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.87,0:23:17.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rainbow!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.62,0:23:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.58,0:23:20.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.75,0:23:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.42,0:23:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw it coming ever since all this began.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.80,0:23:30.39,Signs,,0,0,0,,niji
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.80,0:23:30.39,Signs,,0,0,0,,ni-ji
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.80,0:23:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it started at two o'clock, it had to end with a rainbow!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.68,0:23:33.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another pun...?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.35,0:23:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just when we were commending him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.56,0:23:37.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the point?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.39,0:23:41.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a long-winded joke... and isn't it a bit forced?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.81,0:23:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like always...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.86,0:23:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the design concept Murase-{\i1}san{\i0} showed to Inomata-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.62,0:23:58.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe this shouldn't be thought of as an accident, but a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.91,0:24:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, why was Inomata-{\i1}san{\i0} there?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.50,0:24:03.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.63,0:24:15.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: 'The Case of the Unconfirmed Crash'!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.30,0:24:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's hint: Wrapping band!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.22,0:24:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Guitar!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.85,0:24:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Bass!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.56,0:24:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Drums!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.35,0:24:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Who's on vocals?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.94,0:24:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Not {\i1}that{\i0} kind of band!
